{SECT 0 {PARA 256 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 39 " Getting Started With Basic Cal
culation" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 
312 "Save your current worksheet as number1.mws.  Remember to save fre
quently in case of system shut downs in the middle of a work session! \+
In the text mode (click on the cap T button) place your name(s) and da
te at the top of your worksheet.  At the end of this session you will \+
print out and turn in your worksheet." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 245 "We begin by experimenting with some \+
very basic calculations.  The intent is to learn some basic MAPLE synt
ax, while observing some of the neat features of a Computer Algebra Sy
stem (CAS).  We will also review some basic concepts from arithmetic.
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 842 "Perf
orm the following calculations with MAPLE.  As you do these exercises \+
enter notes and comments onto your worksheet in text mode.  In particu
lar, the author of these worksheets sometimes purposefully leaves off \+
certain required MAPLE syntax.  He is either sadistic or he is trying \+
to make a point.  Let's assume the latter for now. The first example i
s in the first problem below.  A CAS requires some syntaxual thing to \+
tell it when you are through giving it instructions on what you want i
t to do and ready for it to do them.  Try the first calculation just a
s indicated, look at the error message and see if you can figure out w
hat syntax is required by MAPLE to tell it that you are ready for it t
o do its thing. (Place the cursor on the execution line indicated by t
he symbol [> and type in your MAPLE instructions, a. k. a. \"input.\")
" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 7 "1.  6+2" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 117 "Another example of \+
\"omitted\" required MAPLE syntax is in the next problem.  It's more s
ubtle and you may have to ask." }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 10 "2.  2(3
+5)" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" 
{TEXT -1 362 "Can you figure out just what MAPLE was doing to come up \+
with the answer it gave for #2?  In other words \"How did MAPLE interp
ret the operation  2(3+5)?\"  To answer this try some more examples li
ke 2(34), 2(x-6), 2(t). (You can always get a new execution line by cl
icking on [> from the toolbar and ALL QUESTIONS/STATEMENTS IN BOLD FAC
E REQUIRE WRITTEN RESPONSE.)" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 0 "" }{TEXT 
262 7 "ANSWER:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 41 "Continue with the follo
wing calculations:" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "3.  " }{XPPEDIT 18 
0 "(1/5)^2+2" "6#,&*$*&\"\"\"F&\"\"&!\"\"\"\"#F&F)F&" }}{EXCHG {PARA 
0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 44 "Note the
 effect of the next execution line. " }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 9 "evalf(%);" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 264 15 "What did i
t do?" }{TEXT -1 0 "" }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "4.  " }{XPPEDIT 
18 0 "(13-7)/7" "6#*&,&\"#8\"\"\"\"\"(!\"\"F&F'F(" }{TEXT -1 2 "  " }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 30 "Again try the evalf() command." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 9 "evalf(%);" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "5.  " }
{XPPEDIT 18 0 "((8^2-3^3)*(5-22))/(8-4^2)" "6#*(,&*$\"\")\"\"#\"\"\"*$
\"\"$F*!\"\"F(,&\"\"&F(\"#AF+F(,&F&F(*$\"\"%F'F+F+" }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "
> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 30 "Again try t
he evalf() command." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 9 "evalf(
%);" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 4 "6.  " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "(27!)/(10!*1
7!)" "6#*&-%*factorialG6#\"#F\"\"\"*&-F%6#\"#5F(-F%6#\"#<F(!\"\"" }
{TEXT -1 1 " " }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 37 "Note how this compares with the next " }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 16 "binomial(27,10);" }}}{PARA 
0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 43 "7.  Try the MAPLE command binomial(100,50);" }}
{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT 
-1 38 "8.  Compute the corresponding  number " }{XPPEDIT 18 0 "100!/(5
0!*50!) " "6#*&-%*factorialG6#\"$+\"\"\"\"*&-F%6#\"#]F(-F%6#F,F(!\"\"
" }{TEXT -1 2 " ." }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 0 "" }}}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 1 " " }}{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 6 "      " }
{TEXT 257 116 "This expression is called the \"binomial coefficient\" \+
and sometimes referred to as \"100 choose 50.\"  Do you know why?" }}
{PARA 0 "" 0 "" {TEXT -1 143 "9.  Execute the following command sequen
ce and record any relevant observations about what the commands do, au
tomatic features of MAPLE, etc.  " }}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" 
{MPLTEXT 1 0 6 "1+2/3;" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 9 "ev
alf(%);" }}}{EXCHG {PARA 0 "> " 0 "" {MPLTEXT 1 0 12 "1/2+1/3+1/4;" }}
